**Project**: glyph-weave-forge  
**Change**: typst-backend-and-wasm-readiness  
**Archived On**: 2026-03-31  
**Archive Mode**: Engram + filesystem report

## Delivered Scope
- Added an opt-in Typst PDF backend behind `renderer-typst` while preserving the minimal renderer as the default path through the new explicit `renderer-minimal` feature.
- Moved default renderer/resource composition out of core-facing API flow, kept the render port stable, and preserved the memory-first API surface for native and wasm-friendly `--no-default-features` builds.
- Tightened filesystem gating, expanded Typst/configuration error handling, enabled memory-backed Typst asset resolution, and added feature-matrix validation plus updated docs for the new backend contract.

